decision_conditions:
Condition : 3 - No development shall take place above ground level until details and samples of the materials to be used in the construction of the external surfaces of the development hereby permitted have been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The samples/details shall include: 

brick/stonework (including brick, stone, brick framing feature, all mortar colours, joint type, brick bond and sample panels a minimum size of 1m x 1m). 
 
tiles/roof covering;

stone cill finishes;

door and window treatments (including sectional drawings of reveals and cills) and;

All privacy measures (including obscure glazing details) and any other materials/details to be used (including rainwater goods).

The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.
